Make upgrades work: reliable click path + Studio funds that can't be raced

Client boot is fixed (prices + toasts now show), so the remaining failures
were: (1) coins stuck near 0 so every Build was rejected, and (2) the upgrade
billboard TextButtons likely not receiving clicks (the kart ClickDetector works,
so ClickDetectors are the reliable path here).

- StadiumController: clicking the building BODY now upgrades it (build for
  unbuilt active-collect buildings, collect once built) via the building's
  ClickDetector — a reliable fallback to the billboard button.
- Main: guard onPlayerJoin against double-firing in Play Solo (which raced the
  test-funds grant onto the wrong profile copy). Studio coin top-up in the
  income loop keeps coins >=1M so upgrades are always testable.
- Diagnostics: [SvJoin] (server-side coins/stands/isStudio), [SvUpgrade] failure
  reason, and [ClProfile] (what the client receives) so Output shows the truth.

